        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 26 at 2:13AM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 213 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from 7 miles southeast of Oleta
to 7 miles north of Blossom. Movement was northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Redland, Wright City, Kanawha, Rufe, Manchester, Valliant, Kiomatia,
Slim, Ringold, Woodland, and Millerton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
